"Manners will get you places like nothing else can, not education, not money."  Some people disagree.  A speaker at a recent event I spoke at said "take that power!  Sit at that table!" content: Broadway!  To see War Paint!!  It was great.  It is about two makeup industry titans duking it out in a man's world.  Patti Lupone and Christine Ebersole -- and Christine is my cohost for Broadway Backstage!!!  They play Helena Rubinstein and Elizabeth Arden in this musical. Good thing I had on my 8 hour cream.  😊. Isabelle and I made it a great getaway adventure.  She bought a $6 fidget spinner and we got this $20 sweatshirt souvenir for Jack.  Yes, that is Harvey Fierstein with us for a selfie!!!   He was my cohost years ago and somehow remembered.  Must be because he has an amazing memory or maybe because we laughed and cut up the whole time.  Dinner at Joe Allen.  A friend of ours treated!! Trust your gut, risk, believe in yourself, do not give power to critics, support your friends, be kind and empathetic, invest in relationships and reach for your dreams.  Be more afraid of not trying than trying.  Honor and thank your parents.  And let out your inner goof.  This was all on Dr. Farrell's list.  What advice would you add?
